HEADWORD: Melilotic
<hw>Mel`i*lot"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or obtained from, sweet clover or melilot;
specifically, designating an acid of the aromatic series, obtained from
melilot as a white crystalline substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melinae</ent>⟦br⟧
